This paper is primarily focused on privacy in the domain of information retrieval, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. However, the paper also makes use of information theory concepts such as entropy and divergence, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses privacy risks and potential attacks, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also involves the manipulation and analysis of data, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories.
